"The rhino has lost its hair."
[*Similar pronunciation]

26
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:50,500
Not bad.

27
00:01:50,940 --> 00:01:51,780
Good.

28
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:53,340
Good…

29
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:54,740
Godmother,

30
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,860
have you noticed something?

31
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:01,500
Brother Xiao Han tutored me.

32
00:02:01,940 --> 00:02:03,380
Sister Jiayue tutored me too.

33
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,980
But people like them, with good grades,

34
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:08,260
just can't teach me.

35
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,140
On the other hand,

36
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:14,020
we are at the same level

37
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,700
and will look the other way to learn.

38
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,300
We get each other, just us.

39
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:19,420
You're right, Mao Tou.

40
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,380
Though we start off at a lower level,

41
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:22,500
when you get into

42
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,500
No. 2 Middle School

43
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,300
and I become an air stewardess,

44
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,310
we'll give them some...

45
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:29,330
"color see see".
[*Means "impress someone"]

46
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:32,060
We'll definitely give them some

47
00:02:32,580 --> 00:02:33,900
"color see see".

48
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,700
"Color see see". "Color see see"...

49
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:38,100
Mao Tou, put these folded clothes

50
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:38,970
from Jiayue

51
00:02:38,970 --> 00:02:41,140
into her wardrobe,

52
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,040
the first shelf on the left.

53
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,120
The first shelf on the left?

54
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:05,780
Mao Tou?

55
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:06,980
What are you doing?

56
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:14,420
My mom…

57
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:17,020
Godmother told me
to give you some color see see…

58
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:20,380
She's folded your clothes,

59
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,220
and I've put them in.

60
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:23,660
Thanks.

61
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:27,960
Where are you going?

62
00:03:27,970 --> 00:03:29,020
Aren't you going to study?

63
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:37,740
That kid messed up my clothes.

64
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:56,340
The three ways to charge an object,

65
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:58,700
aside from friction and induction,

66
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,620
there's contact electrification.

67
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:01,940
In simple terms,

68
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:03,940
it happens
when an uncharged object

69
00:04:03,940 --> 00:04:05,180
touches a charged one.

70
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:08,740
Do you get it?

71
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:11,340
Got it.

72
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:12,980
Then let me ask you,

73
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:14,740
why do some uncharged objects

74
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:16,700
stay uncharged after they touch
a charged one?

75
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:18,980
Well…

76
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:21,460
Some objects just don't…

77
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:22,700
"connect" with others?

78
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:24,460
"Don't connect"?

79
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:26,140
That's called an insulator!

80
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,690
Finish these two questions.

81
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:34,700
How about we call it a day?

82
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,100
I'll think over what I've learned.

83
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:38,580
You've only been at this for ten minutes!

84
00:04:38,830 --> 00:04:40,440
Do you want to enter No. 2 Middle School?

85
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,180
I do.

86
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,770
Have you never learned sufficient
and necessary conditions?

87
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,580
Let me tell you,

88
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:48,860
having ambition is not
a sufficient condition for success,

89
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:51,500
but effort and seriousness
are necessary conditions.

90
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:53,540
Focus here!

91
00:05:38,860 --> 00:05:40,940
The European delegation
is about to arrive.

92
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:43,860
We need to greet them

93
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:45,740
with the utmost enthusiasm.

94
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:47,260
Understood?

95
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,270
Understood.

96
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:49,760
Louder! Understood?

97
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:50,910
Understood!

98
00:05:54,470 --> 00:05:57,020
We are 11th-grade students.

99
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,140
We are taking a PE class.

100
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:00,860
By the way,

101
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:04,260
we prepared a dancing performance…

102
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,220
To welcome our dear guests.

103
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:20,700
Done?

104
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:23,420
Everyone!

105
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,740
Right face!

106
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,060
Girls,

107
00:06:30,380 --> 00:06:31,780
take two steps forward!

108
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:48,980
Sir, I need to go to the bathroom.

109
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:49,860
Just go ahead.

110
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:50,860
Girls!

111
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:52,100
About-face!

112
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,740
Look, look!

113
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:57,940
Alright!

114
00:06:57,940 --> 00:06:59,000
May I have your attention?

115
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:00,660
Let's quickly review

116
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:01,700
the dance moves, okay?

117
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:03,660
Ka Men,

118
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,620
are you feeling better?

119
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:07,420
How are you now?

120
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:22,980
- Be careful.
- Let me help you.

121
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,540
You've been in there three times already.

122
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,660
Should we go to the infirmary?

123
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:30,420
It's all clean.

124
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,620
Really, it's all clean.

125
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,580
That won't work.

126
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,420
You need to go to the infirmary.

127
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:38,660
Yeah. My mom says

128
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:40,040
if you have unexplained diarrhea,

129
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,660
it's serious.

130
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:41,940
Let's go.

131
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,420
Seriously, no need.

132
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:47,500
I got diarrhea because...

133
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:51,700
I took slimming pills.

134
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:53,820
- Slimming pills?
- Slimming pills?

135
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,140
What kind of pills?

136
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,090
(Saifeiyan Slimming Pills)

137
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:03,660
Those Saifeiyan pills…

138
00:08:03,980 --> 00:08:06,220
They claim anyone can lose 5 kg in a week.

139
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,260
Throw those pills away!

140
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:09,780
These unapproved slimming pills

141
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,540
will either make you
have the runs or vomit.

142
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:19,140
Is this little girl really you?

143
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:22,140
Ka Men was so thin when she was little.

144
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,460
And she was a little host.

145
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,100
Unfortunately, I started gaining weight

146
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,180
in second grade.

147
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:28,820
I changed completely

148
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,420
after just one summer.

149
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:35,340
So, this little boy is truly Lu Yao?

150
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,580
You two knew each other that long ago?

151
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:40,940
But he doesn't remember me.

152
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:45,420
Why don't you tell him?

153
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:49,540
Back then, we danced

154
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:51,460
and hosted together.

155
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:54,460
The teachers always said
we were a perfect pair.

156
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:58,660
But now, he's still the "golden boy",

157
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,340
and I'm no longer the "jade girl".

158
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,780
Ka Men.

159
00:09:03,380 --> 00:09:06,180
So these days, you've been working
so hard to lose weight

160
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:08,820
(Saifeiyan Slimming Pills)
and even taking these pills,

161
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,140
just for Lu Yao?

162
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:12,620
To make him recognize you?

163
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,820
Why go through all this?

164
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:16,660
Just tell him straight up,

165
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,340
"I'm Liu Wanqing from back then."

166
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:19,500
Wouldn't that work?

167
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:24,540
Back then, I was Liu Wanqing,

168
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:25,860
but now…

169
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:27,940
I'm just Ka Men.

170
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:31,060
But Lu Yao doesn't think

171
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:32,620
the current Ka Men is bad.

172
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,380
He still wants to host with you,

173
00:09:34,380 --> 00:09:36,100
and even asked for
your help with English.

174
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:37,180
Yeah.

175
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,420
And you will host together this time,

176
00:09:39,420 --> 00:09:40,940
just like you did back then!

177
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:45,660
Here's an idea.

178
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:47,340
Tomorrow, take this photo with you.

179
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:48,620
After the rehearsal,

180
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:49,660
walk up to him and say,

181
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,660
"I'm the Liu Wanqing from back then!"

182
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:52,820
After ten years,

183
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:55,060
you two are back on the same stage!

184
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:57,060
That would be so meaningful!

185
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:11,060
Look,

186
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:12,180
just extend your hand

187
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:13,540
and you'll look great.

188
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:15,220
- Really?
- Just like a princess!

189
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:17,620
Suddenly, you have that charm.

190
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:25,660
Hey.

191
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:27,860
Go.

192
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,260
Chen.

193
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,940
Stop making assumptions.

194
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,060
It's none of your business.

195
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:37,980
Who's making assumptions?

196
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:39,980
They were talking and laughing,

197
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:42,020
looking so close!

198
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:43,980
That woman

199
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:45,980
seems to live on the 12th floor.

200
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:47,340
Could Liu Songming…

201
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:50,180
have just come out of her apartment?

202
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:53,800
What don't you respond?

203
00:10:53,810 --> 00:10:54,740
I'm talking to you.

204
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,940
What do you expect me to react to?

205
00:10:57,180 --> 00:10:58,020
I'd suggest

206
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,540
you stay out of it.

207
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:01,420
That's Pei's husband!

208
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:04,220
No...

209
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:06,860
I have to tell Pei tomorrow.

210
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:08,420
Stay out of their affairs!

211
00:11:08,740 --> 00:11:10,780
Do you even know what's going on
in their marriage?

212
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,740
As it goes, "Don't meddle in

213
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:15,820
others' business."

214
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,540
If everything works out fine,

215
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:18,940
you'll just end up looking bad.

216
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:30,500
Did you see it right?

217
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:31,620
Was it Liu Songming?

218
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:34,220
Of course, it was him.
I know him well enough.

219
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:36,540
That woman lives in Jinxiu Garden?

220
00:11:36,540 --> 00:11:37,900
Yeah, I've seen her before.

221
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:39,740
She's got big eyes,

222
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:41,380
a slim waist,

223
00:11:41,380 --> 00:11:42,420
long legs,

224
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:43,780
and she walks with a wiggle.

225
00:11:43,780 --> 00:11:44,620
Yes! Exactly!

226
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:45,780
You know her?

227
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:48,220
- Li Qin.
- Li Qin.

228
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:50,860
How dare that Liu Dagui…

229
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:52,860
I think we should

230
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:54,580
think this over carefully.

231
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:56,380
All you saw was those two walking out

232
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:57,500
the front gate.

233
00:11:57,780 --> 00:11:59,260
I think…

234
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:01,020
Xiu'e!

235
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,350
Pei!

236
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:03,340
Xiu'e! Xiu'e!

237
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:04,420
Pei!

238
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,820
I know.

239
00:12:09,140 --> 00:12:10,340
You know?

240
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:12,740
Liu Dagui

241
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:14,060
likes dancing,

242
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,140
which is nothing new.

243
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:17,940
He has a new dance partner, that's all.

244
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:20,660
Pei,

245
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:22,500
that woman is Li Qin!

246
00:12:22,650 --> 00:12:23,500
Remember?

247
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:25,660
She used to always go to the canteen

248
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:28,060
and call out all cutesy,
"Brother Gui! Brother Gui!"

249
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:34,660
Did they really have to dance at home?

250
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:37,300
At home?

251
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:43,580
Pei!

252
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:46,180
Pei, if something's bothering you,

253
00:12:46,180 --> 00:12:47,140
just say it.

254
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:49,060
Now you're making us more worried.

255
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:51,620
What's there to be worried about?

256
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:54,180
Liu Songming likes dancing,

257
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,620
that's all.

258
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,980
Besides, Li Qin is married.

259
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:58,940
Nothing will happen.

260
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,540
That's true.

261
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,220
Li Qin's husband

262
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:06,460
is a pilot, making decent money.

263
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:07,620
She definitely won't let go

264
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,220
of such a steady "meal ticket".

265
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:11,420
Right?

266
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,380
Pei, I'm sorry.

267
00:13:14,380 --> 00:13:15,460
I think I overreacted.

268
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,220
It's okay.

269
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:18,420
Wait!

270
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:21,060
A pilot

271
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:23,220
who's always away at home?

272
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:28,870
Pei,

273
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:32,580
how's Liu Dagui's

274
00:13:32,860 --> 00:13:34,700
waist these days?

275
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:36,700
You're insane!

276
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:38,980
How can you even ask that?

277
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:40,020
I'm just concerned!

278
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:41,300
How am I insane?

279
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:49,620
Bring your feet together.

280
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,020
Open.

281
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:52,820
Push your hands.

282
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:54,540
Curl them!

283
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:55,980
Look.

284
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:06,740
Dinner's ready.

285
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:08,060
Come eat.

286
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:10,460
I'm not eating.

287
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,460
At least eat some vegetables!

